block.p: Last night, the 10 Republican presidential candidates held their debate on Fox News. Now, normally I don't make predictions, but I'm going out on a limb and say I feel the debate was won by the rich white guy.

Last night, the 10 Republican presidential candidates held their debate on Fox News. Now, normally I don't make predictions, but I'm going out on a limb and say I feel the debate was won by the rich white guy.
Yesterday was ''No Gas Day.'' As a protest for high gas prices, people were asked not to buy gas. In fact, I took the $75 I saved on gas and got myself a coffee at Starbucks.
New York City is hosting a four-day global warming summit. But you know, today was such a nice day, they canceled it.

Yesterday, British Prime Minister Tony Blair announced that he will step down next month. After hearing this, President Bush said: ''That's a shame. He's the only world leader who took the time to learn English.''

In a recent interview, Senator John McCain says the last music he bought was the Beach Boys while Mitt Romney says that the last music he bought was Roy Orbison. Apparently, McCain and Romney are both running for president in 1964.
